
This paper uses newly collected household survey data from zzso Ghana, to investigate whether incomes affect acute and chronic health outcomes in settings that can be considered representative for the large and rapidly growing urban centers of sub-Saharan zzso The Time Use and Health Study in zzso collected information on incomes, current health status, and health care use from zzso persons in 1,250 households, each repeatedly sampled on a rolling basis for a period of 13 zzso Data collection took place during September zzso 2010 to capture seasonal zzso The study found that incomes varied widely between households, and that a high fraction of persons lived below the poverty zzso Despite this level of income poverty and an overall remarkably high burden of zzso disease, no systematic differences in zzso and zzso measured health conditions were detected across socioeconomic zzso 

